@* BOUNDARY WITNESS for decision 140: a List that is never written AT ALL -- neither mutated in
   place (decision 106's version signal) nor reassigned wholesale (decision 140's field signal).
   list() would have nothing to subscribe to; a never-written list rendered once is a static tree,
   and that mapping is (still) not implemented. Decision 140 admits the REASSIGNED List; it must
   not invent reactivity for an inert one. *@

<ul id="list">
@foreach (int n in items)
{
    <li @key="n">@n</li>
}
</ul>

@code {
    private List<int> items = new List<int> { 1, 2, 3 };
}
